645\u064f\u0631\u064e\u0642\u0651\u064e\u0639\u064c 754 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0647\u062f \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0626\u0642 \u0644\u0627\u0628\u0646\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36361,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/27\/generosity-zainab\/","url_meta":{"origin":9660,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Zaynab: The generosity of the Prophet\u2019s wife","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Some of the wives of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said to him, \u201cWhich of us will be the quickest to meet you?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThe one with the longest hand.\u201d They measured their hands with sticks and Sawdah had the longest of them,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":1931,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/02\/05\/criticize-no-naming-shaming\/","url_meta":{"origin":9660,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Refutation: The Prophet criticizes without shaming","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported:\u00a0If the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, heard something bad about a man, he would not name him by saying, \u201cWhat is the matter with this person that he says this?\u201d Rather, the Prophet would say, \u201cWhat is the matter with some people who say this?\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":10916,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/03\/ibn-talha-aisha-eloquent\/","url_meta":{"origin":9660,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Talha on Aisha: None were more eloquent than Aisha","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 3, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdul Malik ibn 'Umayr reported: Musa ibn Talha said, \u201cI have not seen anyone more eloquent than Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3884 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0644\u0650\u0643\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064e\u0649 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0637\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062d\u064e\u062f\u064b\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0641\u0652\u0635\u064e\u062d\u064e \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":10923,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/03\/sahabah-aisha-knowledge\/","url_meta":{"origin":9660,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Aisha: Companions go to Aisha for answers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 3, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa reported: We never had a problem occur to us, the companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but that we would ask Aisha and find that she knew something about it. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3883 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064e\u0649 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":10895,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/03\/jibreel-aisha-wife-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":9660,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Aisha: The Prophet is told Aisha is his wife in Hereafter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 3, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Gabriel came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, with her image on a green, silken cloth and he said, \u201cVerily, this is your wife in this world and in the Hereafter.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3880 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u062c\u0650\u0628\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\